      <h2>Fundamental Architecture Difference</h2>

      <div class="architecture-comparison">
        <div class="platform">
          <h3>Cloudflare Workers: Edge Architecture</h3>
          <p>Code runs on 300+ edge locations globally, closest to the user.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Global by default</li>
            <li>Sub-100ms latency from anywhere</li>
            <li>No cold starts</li>
            <li>Stateless execution</li>
            <li>V8 isolate isolation</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="best-for">Best for: Global APIs, fast responses, edge computing</p>
        </div>

        <div class="platform">
          <h3>AWS Lambda: Regional Architecture</h3>
          <p>Code runs in specific AWS regions (us-east-1, eu-west-1, etc.), fixed data center location.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Regional by default</li>
            <li>100-300ms+ latency depending on user location</li>
            <li>Cold starts (100-300ms)</li>
            <li>Stateless or stateful (with external storage)</li>
            <li>Container or isolate isolation</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="best-for">Best for: AWS-ecosystem integration, complex computing, batch processing</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

